is Kay), Align (Nicole Perez-Krueger), Full Coverage (Kristen Foster), Luna=
 (Lauren Auslander), Jill Fritzo, Ame Van Iden, Cheryl Maisel=E2=80=94the l=
ist goes on. And now, 2PM Sharp. That=E2=80=99s not even including Michael =
Nyman=E2=80=99s 2018 exit as C.E.O. of PMK to start an investment and advis=
ory firm.

You don=E2=80=99t need me to tell you that talent P.R. is a much different =
job today than it was even 10 years ago. Now, a well-timed Deuxmoi post can=
 be far more effective than an EW cover. Chicken Shop Date is the new Tonig=
ht Show. Digital creators and the influencer economy are the growth areas. =
And most of the firms offer what is essentially digital brand management as=
 well as traditional P.R. There=E2=80=99s a generational shift
at these firms, too. Publicists, like other reps, grow with their clients. =
And while I=E2=80=99m generalizing: If you look at the PMK client list, the=
re=E2=80=99s a ton of older stars like Kevin Costner, or Billy Crystal, or =
Eddie Murphy. Berger, in a recent presentation to Shea and others, is said =
to have laid out a strategy to grow the more youthful categories.

Don=E2=80=99t get me wrong: PMK still does fine. Those legacy stars, like D=
enzel Washington and Billy Bob Thornton=E2=80=94or even those one generatio=
n down like Chris Pratt=E2=80=94still pay the bills, and the unit is said t=
o be profitable. Hollywood talent P.R. represents a sexy yet small part of =
these large firms=E2=80=99 overall branding and corporate marketing busines=
s. (I=E2=80=99m also pretty sure that Diddy, a big PMK client for a while, =
is no longer on the roster.) While parent IPG doesn=E2=80=99t break out fin=
ancials for PMK, the Octagon unit where PMK resides is doing well=E2=80=94m=
uch better than
IPG overall, whose share price is down 11 percent this year. And PMK isn=E2=
=80=99t alone in suffering major defections; rivals ID PR and 42 West have =
also lost groups who started their own firms.

But PMK is not what it was, and suing over a group of defectors raises a re=
d flag. Regardless of whether they exited the =E2=80=9Cright=E2=80=9D or =
=E2=80=9Cwrong=E2=80=9D way, the message to the broader community is that t=
his loss really hurt PMK, and the leadership doesn=E2=80=99t have a differe=
nt way to respond. It=E2=80=99s tough to spin that.

Finally=E2=80=A6 One Fun Thing=E2=80=A6

